            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "This approach is systematically employed in [20], for example, and can also be used for approximate numerical solution, since the Lagrange multipliers in the case of mixed constraints have a certain regularity, in contrast to the case of pure state constraints.",
            "startOffset": 113570,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 114769,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "Section 3 presents the main result \u2013 a complete set of Pontryagin type necessary optimality (a local maximum principle).",
            "startOffset": 114649,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 150676,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0160",
            "sentence": "The new feature here is that selling of old machine is allowed, which brings state or mixed constraints in the model.",
            "startOffset": 150559,
            "title": "An economic example"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 114931,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "An economic example is discussed in Section 5.",
            "startOffset": 114885,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
