            "title": "Main result: a necessary optimality condition"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 114543,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "The paper is organized as follows.",
            "startOffset": 114509,
            "title": "Introduction"
        },
        {
            "endOffset": 110157,
            "parents": [],
            "secId": "se0010",
            "sentence": "The optimal control theory for age-structured systems has proved to be useful in numerous branches of science: demography (migration or fertility control), population economics (life-cycle investment/education models), health economics (investments in health care), economics (vintage capital models), forestry and fishery (harvesting control), epidemiology (prevention/treatment control), sociology (drug consumption or rumor dynamics and control), etc.",
            "startOffset": 109703,
            "title": "Introduction"
        }
